args: What'd ya wanna see me for, Jakob?
Hold the carrier pigeon. We ain't had three\nwords together, and now ya wanna SPAR?
As a mercenary, I respect you.
You're strong. I want to defeat you\nand prove my own strength.
Bwa ha ha! Well, ya sure as hell\nLOOK determined—I'll give ya that.
All right. Come on, then.\nBut I ain't gonna hold back!
I'm surprised you handled that.\nYer really somethin'!
Hang on. They don't look angry.
I think Jakob has a reason for wanting\nto do this. Let's wait and see\nwhat happens.
But what if they hurt each other?\nI won't stand by and watch this!
Bwaaaa ha ha! Yer good, pal! REAL good!\nI ain't had that much fun in a dog's year!
Guess we gotta call this one a draw.
Heh. Yer all right in my book, Jakob.
And just what sort of best friends\nbeat each other to a pulp?!
What has gotten INTO you two?
Easy, Cleo. We're just havin'\nus a friendly little sparri—
I see nothing friendly about the injuries\nyou have inflicted on one another!
Now be quiet and let me heal you.\n...Honestly, sometimes I do not know\nWHY I put up with these antics.
Well fought, Jakob. I know you're tired,\nbut I was hoping you'd tell me one thing...
I had a realization when talking to you the\nother day, {player_name}.
I respect Ranzal. So if I could defeat him,\nI was sure everything would go well.
And I was certain Cleo would\nunderstand how I feel.
But our fight ended in a draw—AND I\ncaused trouble for Ranzal as well.\nI'll have to buy him a meal later.
It seems I've a long way to go as a man.
Heh. You don't do anything by\nhalf-measures, do you?
But look, if you're brave enough to\nchallenge Ranzal, you're going to be\njust fine in whatever you decide to do.
I hope Cleo realizes how you feel soon.
Jakob?! What are you doing?!\nCome here at once and let me heal you!
